          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-11-16T20:48:52Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to treat the charging of an electric vehicle provided on or near the business premises of the employer as a qualified transportation fringe benefit that is excluded from an employee's gross income. The bill limits the benefit to $175 per month (adjusted for inflation) and specifies requirements for the electric vehicles. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2016-09-28T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
